  						<table width=85% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF FURIOUS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Warrior</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;56</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;9 seconds.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;60 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;56 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>When using this discipline the warrior will automatically riposte every attack landed on them by the opponent they are facing.  This discipline lasts for 9 seconds and has a base reuse time of 60 minutes.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as the warrior gains additional levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>IN FRONT OF YOU</span><b>, By Azbec</b> <small>(3/31/2001)</small><br><br>With mobs at least they only can repost the players in front of them. If I am behind them I hit them like normal. /shrug<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>RIPOSTE VS RIPOSTE</span><b>, By Fatty</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>I have seen log from a person using riposte disipline vs an enraged mob... was about 20 attack per sec for a while there.. noone getting hit.. all was riposted..<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>NOT TRUE</span><b>, By Gromdul alestalker</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>I have Riposted when Auto attack is OFF and the mob was behind me, like when I was pulling.  I pulled a Hillock, turn to run for my group, and hit the thing for 120 damage (critical).  I have also done this to green skeletons while afk in the commons.  One will aggro me, and I'll riposte, whether targeted or not.<P>
ALSO I have done a Crippling Blow while STUNNED.  I have the screen shot.  I was stunned while fighting a MG Craig, I taunted (which you can do while stuned) he attacked me, I riposted and Crippled him for 224 damage with a Mith staff, and he was high red to me.  I also double attacked, but the second swing missed.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>YOU ARE INVUNERABLE</span><b>, By Lerdar</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>When this is up, it is completely impossible for anything to land a melee attack against you, so yes, you are invunerable to melee.  This is a must when fighting mobs like Venril Sathir that hit with a huge lifetap built in.  You need to avoid the lifetap to do any damage.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>ALL MOBS</span><b>, By Hamalek mightyblade</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>I'm not sure about when using the Discipline..but in regular fighting you can riposte ANY mob attacking you...not just the one you have targeted...I KNOW this for sure. Although, as said before, they do have to be in front of you for you to actually hit them, otherwise it would say 'You cannot see your target from here'<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
